column1: Contains a date column for CalLite-CV's time period and fields with the Element name (using the CalLite-CV convention of name_might_include_underscores.element_subname, even though it's different from Sadie's nomenclature, because I'm hoping that leaving them will be less confusing than changing .'s to _'s and making the names harder to read) for all the CalLite-CV records identified in diversionoverview.csv. That .csv contains the combinations required to calculate fraction diverted for each river, but here's one example: for the Upper-Mid Sacramento DSM reach, cell B4 in the overview csv gives the formula RedBluff.Diversion/(RedBluff.Outflow + RedBluff.Diversion), so for 10/2014 the fraction diverted will be 213.1/(6979 + 213.1) = .0296.
